dino_data <- datasaurus_dozen %>%
  filter(dataset == "dino")
ggplot(data = dino_data, mapping = aes(x = x, y = y)) +
  geom_point()

dino_data %>%
  summarize(r = cor(x, y))
## # A tibble: 1 × 1
##         r
##     <dbl>
## 1 -0.0645
star_data <- datasaurus_dozen %>%
  filter(dataset == "star")

  geom_point()

star_data %>%

## 1 -0.0630

There is no great difference between correlations of dino plot and star plot.
